This place is the best Korean-Chinese cuisine / restaurant in the Bergen County, New Jersey. I have been a customer for few years, and I mostly come to this place when I want Korean-Chinese food. The servers and owner are mostly friendly, and the seats are comfortable also. Do not expect for a traditional Chinese style food here though, since it is a fusion restaurant. I like the tea that is provided, and the dessert (sugar-coated sweet potato) also. I mostly come to this place for tangsooyook (fried sweet and sour pork), the crispy texture and the sauce is always delicious. There are many other menus to recommend, such as jjajangmyun (the signature noodles), jjampong (spicy noodle soup), yoosansulbap (rice with seafood), and yooringi (Chinese-styled fried chicken). This restaurant has another place in Manhattan that has a better interior designs and mood, however they are both great in serving delicious food. But, the overall price is a little high, so I recommend this place when you have a special occasion, an event, or for weekend dinners. Moreover, take-outs and deliveries (by other delivery apps like Uber eats) are also available, so this place might be a good option for you considering the current situation of pandemic.
